<% content_for :title, "TheraSaurus Terms of Use" %>
<% content_for :head do %>
  <meta name="description" content="Terms of use for TheraSaurus.">
<% end %>

<article class="w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto rounded-xl bg-white p-8 shadow-lg">
  <%= image_tag "logo.svg", alt: "TheraSaurus", class: "h-16 w-auto mb-8" %>

  <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-plum mb-2">Terms of Use</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Effective Date: May 14, 2026</p>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Agreement to these terms</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      These Terms of Use apply to TheraSaurus websites, applications, and services that link to these terms.
      By using TheraSaurus, you agree to these terms and to the
      <%= link_to "Privacy Policy",
        privacy_policy_path,
        class: "font-semibold text-plum hover:underline focus-visible:underline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-plum rounded cursor-pointer" %><span>.</span>
      If you do not agree, do not use TheraSaurus.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">What TheraSaurus provides</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      TheraSaurus helps pediatric therapists create and manage public profiles so families can find care more easily.
      TheraSaurus may provide account tools, profile tools, directory search, membership billing, credential review,
      and related support.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">No medical advice or therapy</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      TheraSaurus is not a healthcare provider, does not provide therapy, does not provide medical advice,
      and does not create a therapist-client relationship. Families and other visitors are responsible for choosing,
      contacting, and evaluating therapists. In an emergency, call emergency services.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Who may use TheraSaurus</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      Therapist accounts are for adults who can enter a binding agreement. During the first launch phase,
      TheraSaurus supports therapists in the United States. You are responsible for following laws and professional rules that apply to you.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Therapist responsibilities</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">If you create a therapist account, you agree that:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      <li>You have the right to create and manage the profile.</li>
      <li>Your profile information is accurate, current, and not misleading.</li>
      <li>You will keep licenses, credentials, availability, services, locations, pricing, and insurance information up to date.</li>
      <li>You will only upload or publish content you own or have permission to use.</li>
      <li>You will not submit client protected health information unless a separate written agreement allows it.</li>
      <li>You will not use TheraSaurus for unlawful, deceptive, harmful, abusive, or spam activity.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Public profiles and search</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      If your account is eligible for a public profile, TheraSaurus may publish the profile information you provide and include it in directory search.
      We may review, edit formatting, hide, suspend, or remove profiles or profile content that appear inaccurate, misleading, unlawful,
      unsafe, or inconsistent with these terms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Accounts and security</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      You are responsible for activity under your account and for keeping your email account and sign-in methods secure.
      Tell us promptly if you believe your account has been accessed without permission.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Memberships, trials, and billing</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      Paid membership and trial details are shown during checkout. Payments are processed by Stripe.
      A free trial starts only after checkout is completed and a payment method is added. If you skip checkout, no card is collected and no trial starts.
      You can manage supported billing actions through the customer portal when available. Unless the law requires otherwise,
      fees are non-refundable and cancellation takes effect according to the billing settings shown at the time of cancellation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Content license</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      You keep ownership of content you submit. You give TheraSaurus permission to host, store, copy, format, display,
